<subSubSection id="1CD1DC93FF93FFFACDFCA733E11BF8C1" pageId="1" pageNumber="524" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph id="54748F18FF93FFFACDFCA733E11BF8C1" blockId="1.[151,1437,1394,1890]" pageId="1" pageNumber="524">
<emphasis id="66BF530AFF93FFFACDFCA733E112FA54" bold="true" box="[151,274,1394,1420]" pageId="1" pageNumber="524">Diagnosis.</emphasis>
Small-bodied flies with body colour either yellow or black and shiny (
<figureCitation id="CCF0939DFF93FFFAC93AA732E4D7FA55" box="[1105,1239,1394,1421]" captionStart-0="FIGURES 15–18" captionStart-1="FIGURES 19–22" captionStartId-0="10.[151,264,1677,1701]" captionStartId-1="11.[151,264,1975,1999]" captionTargetBox-0="[155,1435,181,1650]" captionTargetBox-1="[181,1435,309,1934]" captionTargetId-0="figure-25@10.[151,1435,181,1654]" captionTargetId-1="figure-83@11.[151,1435,309,1952]" captionTargetPageId-0="10" captionTargetPageId-1="11" captionText-0="FIGURES 15–18. Acerocnema male species, habitus lateral views. 15. A. fasciventris (Malloch); 16. A. merga sp. nov.; 17. A. rufula (Curran); 18. A. vanga sp. nov." captionText-1="FIGURES 19–22. Acerocnema female species, habitus lateral views. 19. A. fasciventris (Malloch); 20. A. merga sp. nov.; 21. A. rufula (Curran); 22. A. vanga sp. nov." figureDoi-0="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4690627" figureDoi-1="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4690629" httpUri-0="https://zenodo.org/record/4690627/files/figure.png" httpUri-1="https://zenodo.org/record/4690629/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="524">Figs 15–22</figureCitation>
). Overall species are weakly bristled. Head is rounded with a variable number of setae. Arista pubescent to bare; length of arista as long as first flagellomere. Postpedicel generally much longer compared to other species of 
<taxonomicName id="93CBF49BFF93FFFAC9F9A7FAE547FA0D" box="[1170,1351,1467,1493]" class="Insecta" family="Scathophagidae" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="524" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="family">Scathophagidae</taxonomicName>
. Palpus spatula-shaped. Setae on head and body yellow or black. Scutal setae are variable in appearance and number, notopleurals, supra-alar, postalar and dorsocentrals distinct. Scutum also with fine soft hairs among the setae. Scutellum always with strong apical and lateral setae. Vein R 
<subScript id="C84F8D5DFF93FFFACFA5A478E2D6F99F" attach="left" box="[718,726,1593,1607]" fontSize="6" pageId="1" pageNumber="524">1</subScript>
usually bare, if setulae present confined to distal portion. Legs with a few extremely weak setae. Abdomen with fine hairs over surface. Male sternite 5 enlarged, deeply bilobate posteriorly, apical lobes narrow to broad. Epandrium on dorsal surface of abdomen, surstylus, cercus and tergite 5 all jutting out from ventral surface of abdomen. Surstylus flattened, slender and at times broadened apically (
<figureCitation id="CCF0939DFF93FFFAC801A4D2E0C4F909" captionStart-0="FIGURES 1–4" captionStart-1="FIGURES 5–8" captionStartId-0="3.[151,264,1698,1722]" captionStartId-1="8.[151,264,1867,1891]" captionTargetBox-0="[167,1431,206,1667]" captionTargetBox-1="[174,1434,267,1822]" captionTargetId-0="figure-17@3.[151,1435,181,1674]" captionTargetId-1="figure-25@8.[151,1435,181,1844]" captionTargetPageId-0="3" captionTargetPageId-1="8" captionText-0="FIGURES 1–4. Male terminalia of Acerocnema. 1. A. fasciventris (Malloch), posterior view; 2. same, lateral view; 3. A. merga sp. nov., posterior view; 4. same, lateral view.Abbreviations: an—anus; cerc—cercus; d sec cerc—dorsal section cercus; epand—epandrium; hypd—hypandrium; pgt—postgonite; sur—surstylus; v sec cerc—ventral section cercus." captionText-1="FIGURES 5–8. Male terminalia of Acerocnema. 5. A. rufula (Curran), posterior view; 6. same, lateral view; 7. A. vanga sp. nov., posterior view; 8. same, lateral view. Abbreviations: cerc—cercus; d sec cerc—dorsal section cercus; pregt—pregonite; sur—surstylus; v sec cerc—ventral section cercus." figureDoi-0="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4690613" figureDoi-1="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4690617" httpUri-0="https://zenodo.org/record/4690613/files/figure.png" httpUri-1="https://zenodo.org/record/4690617/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="524">Figs 1–8</figureCitation>
). Cerci fused basally with deeply divided process underneath. Female terminalia (
<figureCitation id="CCF0939DFF93FFFAC932A4F6E4AAF909" box="[1113,1194,1719,1745]" captionStart="FIGURES 9–14" captionStartId="9.[151,264,1867,1891]" captionTargetBox="[151,1435,193,1823]" captionTargetId="figure-17@9.[151,1435,181,1844]" captionTargetPageId="9" captionText="FIGURES 9–14. Male and female Acerocnema. 9. A. fasciventris (Malloch), male sternite 5, ventral view; 10. A. merga sp. nov., pregonites and postgonites, lateral view; 11. A. merga sp. nov., male sternite 5, ventral view; 12. A. rufula (Curran), male sternite 5, ventral view; 13. A. vanga sp. nov., male sternite 5, ventral view; 14. A. fasciventris (Malloch), female abdomen, lateral view. Abbreviations: cerc—cercus; epiph—epiphallus; epiprct—epiproct; hyprct—hypoproct; pgt—postgonite; ph—phallus; pregt—pregonite." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4690623" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4690623/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="524">Fig. 14</figureCitation>
) very similar to 
<taxonomicName id="93CBF49BFF93FFFAC808A4F6E0EDF92C" authorityName="Rondani" authorityYear="1866" class="Insecta" family="Scathophagidae" genus="Gimnomera" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="524" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="66BF530AFF93FFFAC808A4F6E0EDF92C" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="524">Gimnomera</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. Segments beyond 6 compressed; terminal segments strongly sclerotized and compressed, with spine-like projections.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="1CD1DC93FF93FFFACDACA562E4C5F8BA" pageId="1" pageNumber="524" type="discussion">
<paragraph id="54748F18FF93FFFACDACA562E4C5F8BA" blockId="1.[151,1437,1394,1890]" pageId="1" pageNumber="524">
<emphasis id="66BF530AFF93FFFACDACA562E13BF8E5" bold="true" box="[199,315,1827,1853]" pageId="1" pageNumber="524">Remarks.</emphasis>
DNA barcode data is available for two identified Nearctic species of 
<taxonomicName id="93CBF49BFF93FFFAC92CA562E4D2F8E5" authorityName="Becker" authorityYear="1894" box="[1095,1234,1827,1853]" class="Insecta" family="Scathophagidae" genus="Acerocnema" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="524" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="66BF530AFF93FFFAC92CA562E4D2F8E5" box="[1095,1234,1827,1853]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="524">Acerocnema</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(
<taxonomicName id="93CBF49BFF93FFFAC988A562E52AF8E4" authorityName="Chagnon &amp; Sinclair" authorityYear="2021" box="[1251,1322,1827,1852]" class="Insecta" family="Scathophagidae" genus="Acerocnema" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="524" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="merga">
<emphasis id="66BF530AFF93FFFAC988A562E52AF8E4" box="[1251,1322,1827,1852]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="524">merga</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName id="93CBF49BFF93FFFAC85CA562E0BCF8B8" baseAuthorityName="Malloch" baseAuthorityYear="1920" class="Insecta" family="Scathophagidae" genus="Acerocnema" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="524" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="fasciventris">
<emphasis id="66BF530AFF93FFFAC85CA562E0BCF8B8" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="524">fasciventris</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
) and an additional unidentified species (
<figureCitation id="CCF0939DFF93FFFACFE8A506E2D5F8B9" box="[643,725,1863,1889]" captionStart="FIGURE 27" captionStartId="13.[151,250,1834,1858]" captionTargetBox="[209,1380,202,1783]" captionTargetId="figure-17@13.[151,1436,181,1810]" captionTargetPageId="13" captionText="FIGURE 27. Neighbour-joining tree of 12 specimens of Acerocnema with COI sequences, including unique voucher number (numbers starting with CCDB are from this study), sequence length and GenBank accession number." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4690639" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4690639/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="524">Fig. 27</figureCitation>
) (see Discussion section for further details).
</paragraph>
